.TH "BLUETOOTHCTL-ADVERTISE" "1" "November 2022" "BlueZ" "Linux System Administration"
.SH NAME
bluetoothctl-advertise \- Advertise Submenu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fBbluetoothctl\fP [\-\-options] [advertise.commands]
.sp
This submenu configures LE advertising data and parameters using the
\fBorg.bluez.LEAdvertisement(5)\fP and \fBorg.bluez.LEAdvertisingManager(5)\fP
interfaces.
.SH ADVERTISE OPTIONS COMMANDS
.SS uuids
.sp
Set/Get advertise uuids.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> uuids [uuid1 uuid2 ...]\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.LEAdvertisement(5)\fP property \fBServiceUUIDs\fP
.TP
.B [uuid1 uuid2 ...]
List of UUIDs to advertise (default: none)
.TP
.B Example Show current advertised UUIDs
.nf
\fB> uuids\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise custom 16\-bit service UUID
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x1234\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise custom 32\-bit service UUID
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x12345678\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise custom 128\-bit service UUID
.nf
\fB> uuids 90f95193\-35de\-4306\-a6e9\-699328f15059\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise Battery and Generic Attribute services
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x180F 0x1801\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise Device Information, Battery, and HID services
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x180A 0x180F 0x1812\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise Generic Access service
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x1800\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise Environmental Sensing service
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x181A\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Advertise Pulse Oximeter service
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x183B\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Mix short and full UUID formats
.nf
\fB> uuids 0x180F 12345678\-1234\-5678\-9abc\-123456789abc\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
