.SS discoverable
.sp
Set/Get advertise discoverable.
.sp
For LE discoverable on will set the LE General Discoverable Mode flag to true in
the primary advertisement if on.
.sp
This feature can be changed during advertising, but will only trigger LE General
Discoverable Mode even if you had previously selected discoverable\-timeout this
will be ignored.
.sp
Entering the command by itself will show the status of the setting
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> discoverable [on/off]\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.LEAdvertisement(5)\fP property \fBDiscoverable\fP
.TP
.B [on/off]
Enable/Disable LE General Discoverable Mode
.TP
.B Example Show current discoverable setting
.nf
\fB> discoverable\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Enable LE General Discoverable Mode
.nf
\fB> discoverable on\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Disable discoverable mode
.nf
\fB> discoverable off\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS discoverable\-timeout
.sp
Set/Get advertise discoverable timeout.
.sp
Using this feature in LE will cause the LE Limited Discoverable Mode flag to be
set in the primary advertisement and   The LE General Discoverable Mode flag
will not be set.
.sp
The LE Limited Discoverable Mode flag will automatically turn off after [seconds]
discoverable [on] must be set to use this feature.
.sp
Entering the command by itself will show the current value set.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> discoverable\-timeout [seconds]\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.LEAdvertisement(5)\fP property \fBDiscoverableTimeout\fP
.TP
.B [seconds]
Timeout duration in seconds for LE Limited Discoverable Mode
.TP
.B Example Show current discoverable timeout
.nf
\fB> discoverable\-timeout\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Set LE Limited Discoverable for 30 seconds
.nf
\fB> discoverable\-timeout 30\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Set LE Limited Discoverable for 2 minutes
.nf
\fB> discoverable\-timeout 120\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Set LE Limited Discoverable for 5 minutes
.nf
\fB> discoverable\-timeout 300\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Disable discoverable timeout (unlimited)
.nf
\fB> discoverable\-timeout 0\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS tx\-power
.sp
Show/Enable/Disable TX power to be advertised.
.sp
This sets the TX Power Level field in the advertising packet.
.sp
The value is in dBm and can be between \-127 and 127.
.sp
When this feature is turned on the LE device will advertise its transmit power
in the primary advertisement.
.sp
This feature can be modified while advertising.
.sp
Entering the command by itself will show the current value set.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> tx\-power [on/off]\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.LEAdvertisement(5)\fP property \fBIncludes\fP
.TP
.B [on/off]
Enable or disable TX power advertisement (optional, shows current if omitted)
.TP
.B Example Show current TX power advertisement setting
.nf
\fB> tx\-power\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Enable TX power advertisement with default power
.nf
\fB> tx\-power on\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Disable TX power advertisement
.nf
\fB> tx\-power off\fP
.fi
.sp
